        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Remove legacy suspicious filtering and scanner rollups",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- remove the legacy suspicious visibility/filtering model (`isSuspicious`, suspicious flags, non-suspicious search/list params, non-suspicious leaderboard/index paths, CLI suspicious install prompts)\n- keep `/security-audit` Outcome rendering canonical ClawScan verdict/state directly; VirusTotal, static analysis, dependency registry, and SkillSpector stay supporting evidence/telemetry only\n- keep `clean`, `review`, and `warn` visible/installable; only ClawScan `malicious`, manual moderation blocks, or unrelated availability gates block access\n- update schema, OpenAPI, docs, CLI/API/UI tests, search/list/browse paths, and local seed fixtures to match the new model\n- preserve malicious canonical verdicts during rescans and show canonical pending/error state across detail, audit, version, API, and CLI surfaces\n\n## Rollout / Merge Order\n\nThis PR is stacked on #2354 and is intentionally draft until PR 1 has deployed and its cleanup/backfill has been verified.\n\nBefore merging this PR:\n\n1. Merge and deploy #2354.\n2. Run the PR 1 cursor-based backfills/cleanup in production:\n   - `maintenance:backfillSkillVersionClawScanFields`\n   - `maintenance:backfillPackageReleaseClawScanFields`\n   - `maintenance:cleanupLegacySuspiciousSkillFields`\n   - `maintenance:cleanupLegacySuspiciousDigestFields`\n   - `maintenance:cleanupLegacySuspiciousPackageScanStatuses`\n   - `maintenance:cleanupLegacySuspiciousPackageReleaseScanStatuses`\n3. Verify production data is clean enough for this schema/index narrowing:\n   - no `skills.isSuspicious` / `skillSearchDigest.isSuspicious` fields remain\n   - no `skills.moderationVerdict = \"suspicious\"` remains\n   - no `flagged.review` / `flagged.suspicious` moderation flags remain\n   - canonical `clawScanVerdict` / `clawScanState` are populated for relevant current skill versions and package releases\n   - package/package-release scan-status fields no longer contain legacy `suspicious`\n4. Mark this PR ready, then deploy it. If rollback is needed after this PR, revert this PR and keep the PR 1 canonical verdict data.\n\n## Verification\n\nLocal:\n- `bun run test convex/httpApiV1.handlers.test.ts src/components/SkillSecurityScanResults.test.tsx src/__tests__/skill-detail-page.test.tsx --pool=threads`\n- `bun run test convex/lib/securityPrompt.test.ts scripts/security/run-codex-scan-worker.test.ts convex/securityScan.test.ts src/components/DetailSecuritySummary.test.tsx src/components/SkillSecurityScanResults.test.tsx convex/httpApiV1.handlers.test.ts convex/lib/moderationEngine.test.ts convex/lib/packageSecurity.test.ts convex/packages.public.test.ts convex/skills.rateLimit.test.ts`\n- `bun run test:pw:local-auth`\n- `bun run ci:static`\n- `bun run ci:packages`\n- `bun run ci:types-build`\n- `bun run ci:e2e-http`\n- `bun run ci:unit`\n\nReview:\n- `$autoreview` rerun after fixes. The remaining P1 warning is the expected schema-narrowing warning when reviewing this stacked PR against `origin/main`; this draft PR is gated on the #2354 deploy/backfill/cleanup verification above.\n",
